1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:26,603 --> 00:00:30,053
Mr. Chairman... Please let me go.

3
00:00:38,956 --> 00:00:40,851
What are you doing?

4
00:00:41,814 --> 00:00:43,107
Get him to kneel down.

5
00:00:58,777 --> 00:01:00,100
Honey!

6
00:01:05,638 --> 00:01:07,918
Get up.
You didn't do anything wrong.

7
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:14,444
Gosh, why did you come here?

8
00:01:14,939 --> 00:01:16,897
I'm not here to see you.

9
00:01:18,072 --> 00:01:19,781
I came to see the chairman.

10
00:01:27,753 --> 00:01:30,509
I'm glad you are here too, Gi Bum.

11
00:01:31,192 --> 00:01:33,215
What brought you here?

12
00:01:33,871 --> 00:01:35,888
I am here to show you something.

13
00:01:48,272 --> 00:01:50,027
You know who that is, right?

14
00:01:54,016 --> 00:01:57,433
They would risk their
lives for Director Baek.

15
00:02:06,652 --> 00:02:10,019
Ah... I didn't do that intentionally.
It was an accident!

16
00:02:10,239 --> 00:02:11,754
I was going to just scare him.

17
00:02:11,754 --> 00:02:13,895
But he tripped over and died.

18
00:02:13,895 --> 00:02:16,189
It's true, Tae Soo! It's true!

19
00:02:16,189 --> 00:02:17,646
Dad, please believe me.

20
00:02:18,362 --> 00:02:20,478
Do you know what kind of guy Mr. Son was?

21
00:02:20,478 --> 00:02:23,027
He was a loser, swindler, and gambler!

22
00:02:23,027 --> 00:02:26,721
He lost all of your three
billion won at the casino!

23
00:02:29,580 --> 00:02:32,026
It says the borrower is my husband, huh?

24
00:02:33,050 --> 00:02:35,877
If you and I were drowning in the water

25
00:02:36,313 --> 00:02:38,651
Which of us do you think
Tae Soo would save first?

26
00:02:38,675 --> 00:02:41,683
If this place is on fire
who would he save first?

27
00:02:42,383 --> 00:02:45,085
He risked his life for you for 20 years.

28
00:02:45,085 --> 00:02:47,162
But framing him for a
murder was not enough.

29
00:02:47,162 --> 00:02:50,358
You had to make him sign an
IOU for three billion won?

30
00:03:07,689 --> 00:03:09,002
Let's go, Honey.

31
00:03:18,461 --> 00:03:19,972
Dad...

32
00:03:21,681 --> 00:03:23,270
What an idiot.

33
00:03:23,481 --> 00:03:25,116
Dummy!

34
00:03:29,008 --> 00:03:31,199
<i>[Episode 4]</i>

35
00:03:37,271 --> 00:03:38,937
Oh, gosh!

36
00:03:39,132 --> 00:03:40,580
Ah...

37
00:03:45,826 --> 00:03:46,938
Eun Ok!

38
00:03:49,581 --> 00:03:52,070
You don't have to thank me.

39
00:03:52,395 --> 00:03:56,270
The one who saved you is the lady in
charge of the neighborhood council.

40
00:03:56,764 --> 00:03:57,811
Huh?

41
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:10,462
Kyung Mee.

42
00:04:10,462 --> 00:04:14,018
<i>Eun Ok, did you hear about Tae Soo's
IOU for three billion won?</i>

43
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:18,961
Gosh...

44
00:04:19,021 --> 00:04:22,139
Eun Ok, what brought you
here at this hour?

45
00:04:22,139 --> 00:04:25,766
I'm sorry... but can I check
the black box footage from last week?

46
00:04:26,144 --> 00:04:29,755
<i>My husband said it got deleted
because it had a small memory card.</i>

47
00:04:29,884 --> 00:04:32,541
Tae Soo asked about it last night too.

48
00:04:32,541 --> 00:04:33,944
Is something going on?

49
00:04:36,511 --> 00:04:38,045
<i>Am I fooling a ghost here?</i>

50
00:04:38,045 --> 00:04:41,661
<i>I saw it with my own eyes.
You can't deny it!</i>

51
00:04:41,831 --> 00:04:45,343
You threw away trash here
at 11:40 PM last night.

52
00:04:45,343 --> 00:04:46,759
Huh?

53
00:04:46,759 --> 00:04:48,562
You did it at 11:13 PM the night before.

54
00:04:48,562 --> 00:04:49,980
Should I say the seconds too?

55
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:52,622
It's not like you're poor.
Buy your own trash bags!

56
00:04:52,622 --> 00:04:54,454
Chairwoman of the Neighborhood Council!

57
00:04:54,454 --> 00:04:55,615
Seriously... Huh?

58
00:04:55,615 --> 00:04:57,538
- Ma'am!
- You scared me!

59
00:04:57,571 --> 00:05:00,050
Ma'am! How do you know that?

60
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:02,651
How you do you know they
threw away trash here?

61
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:05,370
How? Please answer me!

62
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:10,855
Over there.

63
00:05:21,896 --> 00:05:24,221
What's wrong?
Where are you going?

64
00:05:24,221 --> 00:05:27,115
I have to say what I couldn't
say to the chairman!

65
00:05:27,115 --> 00:05:28,516
Are you crazy?

66
00:05:29,423 --> 00:05:32,401
Why do you think I went to
him, not to the police?

67
00:05:32,401 --> 00:05:34,911
That way, you could live and
it wouldn't get too big.

68
00:05:34,911 --> 00:05:37,077
What is it that you want to do there?

69
00:05:42,610 --> 00:05:44,093
Gosh.

70
00:05:44,697 --> 00:05:47,060
Didn't you see how pale his face turned?

71
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:49,536
And Baek Gi Bum had the sorriest excuse!

72
00:05:49,536 --> 00:05:51,370
They are that kind of people!

73
00:05:51,834 --> 00:05:53,129
What will do you now?

74
00:05:53,129 --> 00:05:56,300
We've seen everything about them.
You can't go back!

75
00:06:12,298 --> 00:06:14,339
I, Yoon Tae Soo...!

76
00:06:14,339 --> 00:06:16,964
I quit as of today!

77
00:06:16,987 --> 00:06:20,391
Even if I make one million won a month

78
00:06:20,391 --> 00:06:22,824
You will be able to sleep
well at night, Eun Ok!

79
00:06:23,494 --> 00:06:26,439
Geez, I'm so glad to hear that!

80
00:06:26,439 --> 00:06:28,446
You finally grew up!

81
00:06:28,446 --> 00:06:30,853
Now that I decided to do that

82
00:06:30,930 --> 00:06:32,821
it feels great!

83
00:06:32,821 --> 00:06:35,064
Sure! Why not!

84
00:06:35,064 --> 00:06:39,427
I'll make it work no matter how
little money you bring home.

85
00:06:39,494 --> 00:06:42,622
We won't send the kids to
the afterschool programs.

86
00:06:42,622 --> 00:06:46,024
Sung Min and Soo Min will dance
around because they're happy!

87
00:06:46,024 --> 00:06:47,598
Ding Dong Dang!

88
00:06:47,598 --> 00:06:49,834
Our house is the chairman's.

89
00:06:49,834 --> 00:06:52,189
We can just live on the street!

90
00:06:52,189 --> 00:06:53,903
Let's buy a tent!

91
00:06:53,903 --> 00:06:56,435
There are many good ones!
Where should we put it up?

92
00:06:56,435 --> 00:06:58,896
We need to use water and a restroom.

93
00:06:58,896 --> 00:07:00,576
Maybe right next to a public restroom?

94
00:07:00,576 --> 00:07:02,744
We can handle the smell...

95
00:07:02,744 --> 00:07:06,172
And we can just eat
the free samples at the market!

96
00:07:06,172 --> 00:07:10,000
Or we can get free meals
at Mom's senior center!

97
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,524
I love that!

98
00:07:11,524 --> 00:07:15,031
We could even save some
money if we did that!

99
00:07:15,211 --> 00:07:18,232
I'm still going to spend
5,000 won on Lotto tickets.

100
00:07:18,232 --> 00:07:19,675
Of course.

101
00:07:20,185 --> 00:07:21,694
Without that...

102
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:25,129
What hope would we have to hold on to?

103
00:07:25,396 --> 00:07:28,843
Geez, why do you say that?

104
00:07:28,843 --> 00:07:31,887
I'm losing my appetite for
alcohol over the word, hope.

105
00:07:35,374 --> 00:07:36,485
Gosh.

106
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,072
Geez.

107
00:07:41,072 --> 00:07:42,158
Geez.

108
00:07:42,158 --> 00:07:44,134
- I'm going to die.
- I'm going to die.

109
00:07:44,822 --> 00:07:46,456
What's going on here?

110
00:07:46,456 --> 00:07:47,649
Oh?

111
00:07:47,649 --> 00:07:50,519
Madam Lee Choon Boon!

112
00:07:50,519 --> 00:07:52,379
What the heck is going on?

113
00:07:52,379 --> 00:07:54,019
Hey, how much did you drink?

114
00:07:54,019 --> 00:07:55,475
It just happened.

115
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:58,170
Oh, Mother!

116
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:01,163
Please don't be harsh.

117
00:08:01,163 --> 00:08:04,346
Today, I did something amazing!

118
00:08:04,346 --> 00:08:08,274
Today I saved your son, Yoon Tae Soo!

119
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:12,562
You should praise me for that, Mother.

120
00:08:12,797 --> 00:08:18,019
If you praise me, I will forget
everything and forgive you!

121
00:08:19,317 --> 00:08:21,327
What the heck is she talking about?

122
00:08:21,327 --> 00:08:23,459
Get off me! You are stinky!

123
00:08:23,459 --> 00:08:25,483
Give me a high five!

124
00:08:25,483 --> 00:08:27,362
High five!

125
00:08:27,362 --> 00:08:28,846
Geez, calm down!

126
00:08:28,846 --> 00:08:30,072
Wow!

127
00:08:30,088 --> 00:08:33,159
Gosh, go in the room.
The kids are watching.

128
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,801
Why? Go on, Mom!

129
00:08:34,801 --> 00:08:37,288
Give me an interview!

130
00:08:37,288 --> 00:08:40,452
Please make me look
beautiful like an actress.

131
00:08:40,452 --> 00:08:43,756
My ugly, pretty daughter!

132
00:08:44,726 --> 00:08:46,106
Drink some water, Mom.

133
00:08:46,125 --> 00:08:47,171
Good.

134
00:08:47,187 --> 00:08:49,750
My son was here too!

135
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:52,927
Did you cry? Why are your eyes so red?

136
00:08:53,191 --> 00:08:55,143
Who cried?

137
00:08:55,143 --> 00:08:57,469
Sung Min!

138
00:08:57,469 --> 00:09:00,014
You're the best, my son!

139
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:02,538
You know what my wishes are.

140
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:06,120
No matter what, you must
go to a college in Seoul.

141
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,801
At least one of the top three schools!

142
00:09:07,815 --> 00:09:10,013
If you go to Seoul University

143
00:09:10,013 --> 00:09:12,774
I will dance in the middle
of a road in Seoul!

144
00:09:12,792 --> 00:09:17,202
Seoul University! My son got
admitted to Seoul University!

145
00:09:17,202 --> 00:09:20,321
My son goes to Seoul University!

146
00:09:20,344 --> 00:09:22,491
My son goes to Seoul University!

147
00:09:22,491 --> 00:09:23,702
Mom!

148
00:09:23,702 --> 00:09:25,869
Mom...

149
00:09:25,869 --> 00:09:27,863
Mom loves Seoul University!

150
00:09:27,863 --> 00:09:30,254
I'm sorry, Mom. I'll take her.

151
00:09:30,254 --> 00:09:31,767
Let's go, honey.

152
00:09:31,767 --> 00:09:32,860
- Let's go.
- Love ya!

153
00:09:32,860 --> 00:09:35,719
Mother! I love you!

154
00:09:35,719 --> 00:09:38,698
- I love you, Soo Min!
- Let's go to sleep.

155
00:09:38,698 --> 00:09:40,883
What a beautiful night!

156
00:09:40,918 --> 00:09:42,238
Love you!

157
00:09:42,238 --> 00:09:43,918
Oh, my blood pressure.

158
00:09:43,918 --> 00:09:46,230
Oh, yes! I got you, Mom.

159
00:09:46,230 --> 00:09:47,961
I love you!

160
00:09:47,961 --> 00:09:50,894
Oh...

161
00:09:51,225 --> 00:09:52,291
Geez.

162
00:09:52,835 --> 00:09:54,980
Geez. Let me see.

163
00:09:57,402 --> 00:10:01,221
Why is it that life sucks?

164
00:10:53,177 --> 00:10:54,678
Do you remember this place?

165
00:10:55,504 --> 00:10:57,224
How can I forget?

166
00:10:57,224 --> 00:11:00,192
Without you, this would
have been my burial site.

167
00:11:00,317 --> 00:11:02,335
Was it about 15 years ago?

168
00:11:02,797 --> 00:11:06,355
You and I hid here and barely survived.

169
00:11:07,991 --> 00:11:11,349
I made up my mind then.

170
00:11:12,164 --> 00:11:14,644
From now on, Tae Soo is my son.

171
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:19,586
Tae Soo.

172
00:11:23,206 --> 00:11:24,524
About Gi Bum...

173
00:11:25,192 --> 00:11:28,519
I'll just think that he doesn't exist.
So do whatever you want with him.

174
00:11:29,177 --> 00:11:31,869
I'll send him to the Philippines
if you say so.

175
00:11:31,869 --> 00:11:34,941
Even if you turn him to the
police, I can't say much.

176
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:41,057
How will you live without Gi Bum?

177
00:11:41,057 --> 00:11:43,889
Is he my only child?

178
00:11:45,546 --> 00:11:47,585
I have you too, Tae Soo.

179
00:11:49,610 --> 00:11:51,716
It's all my fault.

180
00:11:54,205 --> 00:11:59,090
A horse running in the wild doesn't have
the time to take care of his stable.

181
00:12:00,058 --> 00:12:02,551
That's how I spoiled Gi Bum.

182
00:12:03,176 --> 00:12:05,057
Now that he's so immature

183
00:12:05,442 --> 00:12:08,317
he's becoming a disgrace to me.

184
00:12:16,643 --> 00:12:17,730
Mr. Chairman.

185
00:12:25,053 --> 00:12:27,048
Will you do as I say?

186
00:12:27,393 --> 00:12:28,451
What do you want?

187
00:12:28,451 --> 00:12:30,390
Promise me first.

188
00:12:36,821 --> 00:12:38,154
Gi Bum...

189
00:12:38,989 --> 00:12:40,876
He's my dearest friend.

190
00:12:41,376 --> 00:12:43,326
I'm the one who owes him.

191
00:12:44,018 --> 00:12:46,518
Anyway, he took care of
someone who deserved to die.

192
00:12:46,518 --> 00:12:48,854
And I'm proven innocent.

193
00:12:49,331 --> 00:12:51,644
So I am the one who
owes him a drink.

194
00:12:53,645 --> 00:12:54,884
Do you mean it?

195
00:12:55,777 --> 00:12:59,280
Do you think you can
let go of everything?

196
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,461
Yes.

197
00:13:00,888 --> 00:13:03,623
You always said if the result
is good, everything is good.

198
00:13:03,623 --> 00:13:05,533
This is that kind of situation.

199
00:13:05,686 --> 00:13:07,725
Then... what about the movie?

200
00:13:07,803 --> 00:13:09,798
Of course I should make it.

201
00:13:09,798 --> 00:13:12,811
I was even on TV as a movie maker.

202
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:16,442
Also, I should make sure you look good.

203
00:13:21,568 --> 00:13:22,807
Tae Soo.

204
00:13:23,253 --> 00:13:24,928
Geez, look at you.

205
00:13:24,928 --> 00:13:27,475
You got so thin because
of all that stress.

206
00:13:28,807 --> 00:13:30,499
Don't worry about the movie.

207
00:13:30,572 --> 00:13:32,340
I will take care of it.

208
00:13:59,975 --> 00:14:02,591
Why are you outside? It's cold!

209
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:06,075
Honey, are you really okay?

210
00:14:06,075 --> 00:14:08,013
Of course I am.

211
00:14:11,690 --> 00:14:14,722
Thank you for coming back safely.

212
00:14:15,385 --> 00:14:16,480
Oh, man!

213
00:14:17,581 --> 00:14:20,717
People might think we are
shooting a movie here.

214
00:14:22,322 --> 00:14:25,476
You're frozen. Let's go in.
You might catch a cold.

215
00:14:26,860 --> 00:14:28,105
Are you sober now?

216
00:14:28,105 --> 00:14:30,336
I was all over the place
last night, right?

217
00:14:30,575 --> 00:14:33,243
I don't know. I saw nothing.

218
00:14:33,246 --> 00:14:35,284
Soo Min took a video of it.

219
00:14:35,475 --> 00:14:38,418
- It's cold!
- Why is it so cold?

220
00:14:41,827 --> 00:14:44,177
You just recovered from a cold.

221
00:14:44,177 --> 00:14:45,291
Are you up?

222
00:14:45,724 --> 00:14:48,746
You haven't slept much
since you came home late.

223
00:14:48,746 --> 00:14:50,351
Is something going on?

224
00:14:50,879 --> 00:14:54,586
Director Baek didn't come home
last night.

225
00:14:54,910 --> 00:14:57,217
I can't really talk about it.

226
00:14:57,481 --> 00:14:58,938
Just pretend you don't know.

227
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:02,554
I'm disappointed if you do this.

228
00:15:02,662 --> 00:15:04,624
I can't blame anyone.

229
00:15:05,330 --> 00:15:08,892
He's like money bouncing
around, not doing anything good.

230
00:15:09,697 --> 00:15:13,817
It's my fault. I'm always on his case.

231
00:15:15,628 --> 00:15:18,393
It feels like I lost two sons
at the same time.

232
00:15:19,831 --> 00:15:23,067
How about making him a family?

233
00:15:23,466 --> 00:15:27,249
He's lost because he has
no family to take care of.

234
00:15:27,735 --> 00:15:31,155
That's why he keeps causing
trouble for you.

235
00:15:33,745 --> 00:15:38,071
You know his ex-wife and
daughter came back to Daejeon?

236
00:15:38,817 --> 00:15:40,653
Don't even mention them.

237
00:15:41,558 --> 00:15:42,985
I have no business with them.

238
00:15:46,288 --> 00:15:47,537
Oh...

239
00:15:47,764 --> 00:15:51,335
I used less whipped cream
and put lots of fruits.

240
00:15:51,429 --> 00:15:55,135
Was it obvious I was on a diet?

241
00:15:57,033 --> 00:15:59,510
Why don't you sit if you aren't too busy?

242
00:15:59,510 --> 00:16:00,650
Should I?

243
00:16:04,032 --> 00:16:06,201
I know I might be rude to say this...

244
00:16:06,697 --> 00:16:09,264
But I know about you and Director Baek.

245
00:16:11,005 --> 00:16:12,658
It's all in the past.

246
00:16:13,628 --> 00:16:14,879
Perhaps...

247
00:16:15,645 --> 00:16:18,881
The chairman doesn't like me
coming back here...

248
00:16:18,881 --> 00:16:20,303
Are you here to tell me that?

249
00:16:20,303 --> 00:16:22,788
Oh, no. Please don't misunderstand.

250
00:16:22,788 --> 00:16:24,990
Then... why?

251
00:16:26,070 --> 00:16:30,245
Well.... let's say I'm just
curious about you, Do Kyung.

252
00:16:30,383 --> 00:16:33,315
It's like, you are attracted
to certain people.

253
00:16:33,546 --> 00:16:37,009
You're someone I can relate to.

254
00:16:38,982 --> 00:16:41,750
Wow, you and I are definitely
thinking the same thing!

255
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:44,236
You felt so familiar from the beginning.

256
00:16:44,236 --> 00:16:47,416
Where did you live in Seoul?

257
00:16:47,461 --> 00:16:51,169
Seoul...? Mostly... in Gangnam...

258
00:16:51,749 --> 00:16:52,857
But...

259
00:16:52,857 --> 00:16:57,181
You wouldn't have seen me
because I lived abroad mostly.

260
00:16:58,136 --> 00:16:59,586
Well...

261
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:03,285
Could it be the Indian consul's
party last summer?

262
00:17:03,509 --> 00:17:05,845
Didn't you come to the party?

263
00:17:06,018 --> 00:17:07,499
Not at all.

264
00:17:07,682 --> 00:17:10,643
Well, maybe because you are so beautiful

265
00:17:10,643 --> 00:17:12,729
I might have thought you
were an actress I knew.

266
00:17:12,729 --> 00:17:15,230
Oh, please...!

267
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:20,237
I would like to treat you like
my own sister from now on.

268
00:17:20,237 --> 00:17:21,736
If that's okay with you.

269
00:17:22,893 --> 00:17:24,019
Thank you.

270
00:17:26,346 --> 00:17:28,617
Please have some, Sister.

271
00:17:29,491 --> 00:17:30,935
Thank you.

272
00:17:43,502 --> 00:17:46,551
<i>[Missing Person]</i>

273
00:17:48,844 --> 00:17:51,198
What the heck! What is this, Boss?

274
00:17:53,016 --> 00:17:54,055
Gosh.

275
00:17:54,805 --> 00:17:56,452
What are you doing? Take it off!

276
00:17:56,609 --> 00:17:57,827
Take it off?

277
00:17:57,901 --> 00:18:00,311
I said take them off!

278
00:18:05,409 --> 00:18:06,463
Hey.

279
00:18:06,463 --> 00:18:07,842
<i>Did you see them, honey?</i>

280
00:18:07,842 --> 00:18:09,320
<i>Where the heck are you?</i>

281
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:11,968
Ma'am...

282
00:18:12,510 --> 00:18:16,760
You can't report a missing person
until it's been five years.

283
00:18:16,815 --> 00:18:19,190
For now, you can report a runaway.

284
00:18:19,190 --> 00:18:21,037
I said it's an accident, not a runaway.

285
00:18:21,037 --> 00:18:24,724
You can't insist that
when there's no evidence.

286
00:18:24,888 --> 00:18:27,443
There's an order of business
in everything.

287
00:18:27,443 --> 00:18:30,759
My goodness, you are so dense.

288
00:18:30,759 --> 00:18:32,973
That's why you are still
in that position.

289
00:18:35,326 --> 00:18:37,112
Were you born in August?

290
00:18:37,112 --> 00:18:38,165
Year of Dog?

291
00:18:40,641 --> 00:18:42,717
How do you know...?

292
00:18:42,717 --> 00:18:44,221
What's the date of your birth?

293
00:18:46,492 --> 00:18:47,528
It's eighth.

294
00:18:51,269 --> 00:18:53,998
Oh... geez.

295
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:57,701
It's one of the hottest days of the year.

296
00:18:57,701 --> 00:18:59,006
Gosh.

297
00:18:59,682 --> 00:19:02,116
You went through a lot, right?

298
00:19:02,282 --> 00:19:04,661
The spirit says a good thing
will happen in the new year.

299
00:19:04,661 --> 00:19:06,167
Yeah?

300
00:19:09,196 --> 00:19:12,175
She says watch your steps.

301
00:19:12,696 --> 00:19:14,536
She says dig with your front legs.

302
00:19:17,946 --> 00:19:19,868
Please help me find him.

303
00:19:20,625 --> 00:19:22,564
My son is missing.

304
00:19:23,142 --> 00:19:24,833
Please help me find my son.

305
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:26,271
Please help!

306
00:19:26,271 --> 00:19:28,144
He talks like a Seoulite.

307
00:19:37,576 --> 00:19:40,920
Gosh, we're going to die from running!

308
00:19:40,982 --> 00:19:43,503
Honey, are we having a punishment?

309
00:19:43,503 --> 00:19:45,531
What are you doing? Take them off!

310
00:19:46,035 --> 00:19:48,317
They are all over the town!

311
00:19:48,317 --> 00:19:50,019
Someone's there!

312
00:19:56,300 --> 00:19:57,719
It could have been bad.

313
00:19:57,847 --> 00:19:59,511
- Are they gone?
- Really?

314
00:19:59,511 --> 00:20:00,582
Yeah.

315
00:20:03,347 --> 00:20:05,483
Be careful! We almost got caught!

316
00:20:05,483 --> 00:20:08,713
I was so focused I didn't see them!

317
00:20:08,839 --> 00:20:11,557
It drives me nuts! When are we
going to take them all off?

318
00:20:11,557 --> 00:20:13,945
Are we going to be okay?

319
00:20:13,945 --> 00:20:15,631
What do you mean?
Did we do something?

320
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:17,892
Just focus! Okay?

321
00:20:18,638 --> 00:20:20,561
Over there! It's totally covered!

322
00:20:20,561 --> 00:20:23,303
Be natural. Be natural.

323
00:20:23,303 --> 00:20:25,698
Be natural...

324
00:20:32,526 --> 00:20:33,815
Oh...

325
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:36,104
What are the bags for?

326
00:20:36,159 --> 00:20:38,884
Oh... it's nothing.

327
00:20:38,884 --> 00:20:41,625
Say hello. She's my friend.

328
00:20:41,625 --> 00:20:43,933
- Oh, hello.
- Hello.

329
00:20:44,198 --> 00:20:45,634
You must be her son.

330
00:20:45,737 --> 00:20:47,471
And you are her daughter in-law.

331
00:20:47,713 --> 00:20:48,857
Yes.

332
00:20:49,335 --> 00:20:51,084
I'll bring something to eat.

333
00:20:51,084 --> 00:20:52,116
Okay.

334
00:20:52,266 --> 00:20:54,739
Sit over here.

335
00:20:54,866 --> 00:20:55,902
Sure.

336
00:20:59,632 --> 00:21:01,142
Oh, Tae Soo!

337
00:21:01,663 --> 00:21:04,045
This is an amazing coincidence!

338
00:21:04,045 --> 00:21:08,390
How could I run into the
Shaman of Mia-ri there like that!

339
00:21:08,865 --> 00:21:10,468
Shaman of what?

340
00:21:10,468 --> 00:21:14,772
She says she's a famous shaman in Seoul.

341
00:21:14,835 --> 00:21:18,105
She has hundreds of regulars!

342
00:21:18,392 --> 00:21:20,382
You know what's even more interesting?

343
00:21:20,847 --> 00:21:22,117
What is it?

344
00:21:22,446 --> 00:21:24,654
She's the mother of the man.

345
00:21:24,736 --> 00:21:26,480
Who is that man?

346
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:29,003
The man you're making a movie with!

347
00:21:29,003 --> 00:21:31,538
I told him he had a lucky face.

348
00:21:33,506 --> 00:21:34,530
What?

349
00:21:34,711 --> 00:21:36,201
Why are you so surprised?

350
00:21:37,332 --> 00:21:39,901
We were just worried about him.

351
00:21:39,901 --> 00:21:43,380
Because his business partner
has been out of touch.

352
00:21:46,088 --> 00:21:48,574
I see a knife in your physiognomy.

353
00:21:48,627 --> 00:21:49,682
Pardon?

354
00:21:49,919 --> 00:21:51,233
What does that mean?

355
00:21:51,892 --> 00:21:55,353
Actually he's well-known
for his fist in Daejeon.

356
00:21:55,353 --> 00:21:56,578
- Mom...
- Yeah?

357
00:21:56,634 --> 00:21:57,875
Okay.

358
00:21:57,875 --> 00:21:59,965
Why did you have one child?

359
00:22:00,673 --> 00:22:02,521
You didn't want a son?

360
00:22:06,868 --> 00:22:08,126
It's not true.

361
00:22:08,126 --> 00:22:10,847
We have a son. My oldest is a son.

362
00:22:12,212 --> 00:22:16,112
Well... he doesn't look like you at all!

363
00:22:16,112 --> 00:22:19,957
That's why he's a good student at school.

364
00:22:19,957 --> 00:22:21,991
He ranks first in his class.

365
00:22:21,991 --> 00:22:26,413
Gosh, this isn't the time for
me to tell others' fortunes.

366
00:22:26,544 --> 00:22:28,497
My son is missing!

367
00:22:28,497 --> 00:22:29,622
Okay.

368
00:22:29,634 --> 00:22:33,421
Anyway she'll stay with us
until she finds her son.

369
00:22:33,421 --> 00:22:35,156
Just know that, okay?

370
00:22:35,190 --> 00:22:36,299
Sure...

371
00:22:42,875 --> 00:22:45,808
Get him! Get him!

372
00:22:45,992 --> 00:22:47,807
Get him!

373
00:22:49,117 --> 00:22:50,997
Hey, beat him!

374
00:22:54,067 --> 00:22:55,536
Stop!

375
00:22:57,137 --> 00:22:58,180
You!

376
00:23:07,654 --> 00:23:09,673
Step aside.

377
00:23:26,182 --> 00:23:27,334
Huh?

378
00:23:28,738 --> 00:23:31,079
Mr. Son, are you okay?

379
00:23:32,585 --> 00:23:34,461
- I'm fine.
- Huh?

380
00:23:34,461 --> 00:23:36,917
A dead body doesn't hurt.

381
00:23:37,981 --> 00:23:39,380
Oh... oh...

382
00:23:39,670 --> 00:23:41,382
Ah!

383
00:23:47,176 --> 00:23:49,227
See you soon.

384
00:23:56,569 --> 00:23:57,781
What's wrong?

385
00:23:58,817 --> 00:24:01,615
No... it was a dream.

386
00:24:03,744 --> 00:24:05,423
I had a nightmare.

387
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:08,705
Could it be that... she knows something?

388
00:24:08,943 --> 00:24:11,286
You saw her scary eyes, right?

389
00:24:11,286 --> 00:24:12,372
Yeah.

390
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:17,210
Well, it can't be.

391
00:24:17,410 --> 00:24:20,267
If she knew something
she would've reported it.

392
00:24:20,267 --> 00:24:21,632
Sleep now.

393
00:24:21,632 --> 00:24:23,929
I have something to do.

394
00:24:24,054 --> 00:24:25,144
Okay.

395
00:24:37,707 --> 00:24:39,136
You scared me!

396
00:24:39,136 --> 00:24:41,307
What are you doing here?

397
00:24:41,307 --> 00:24:42,714
I'm praying!

398
00:24:42,714 --> 00:24:44,267
My goodness!

399
00:24:44,317 --> 00:24:47,558
What are you doing?
You totally scared me!

400
00:24:47,558 --> 00:24:48,558
Geez.

401
00:24:49,977 --> 00:24:51,707
Did you have a nightmare?

402
00:24:52,592 --> 00:24:53,751
Pardon?

403
00:24:55,282 --> 00:24:56,566
No...

404
00:24:57,220 --> 00:25:00,272
I came out to go to the bathroom.

405
00:25:00,409 --> 00:25:03,440
Please answer me!

406
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:08,134
My poor son, Se Yoon!

407
00:25:08,134 --> 00:25:10,147
Please answer me!

408
00:25:15,288 --> 00:25:18,252
My poor son, Se Yoon!

409
00:25:18,252 --> 00:25:20,949
Please answer me!

410
00:25:36,859 --> 00:25:39,193
Just like that, that feeling!

411
00:25:39,193 --> 00:25:40,380
Pavane!

412
00:25:40,482 --> 00:25:42,431
Cry if you want to cry.

413
00:25:42,431 --> 00:25:45,382
Don't save your tears if it's for an art!

414
00:25:46,433 --> 00:25:48,330
Should I make you shed tears and blood?

415
00:25:48,384 --> 00:25:49,443
Pardon?

416
00:25:49,627 --> 00:25:50,702
Huh?

417
00:25:50,702 --> 00:25:54,423
I have no comments on that.

418
00:25:56,173 --> 00:25:58,788
Is this all you can do, huh?

419
00:25:59,827 --> 00:26:01,906
That's the most expensive item here.

420
00:26:01,906 --> 00:26:03,509
You can break anything except for that!

421
00:26:03,509 --> 00:26:06,063
It's the most expensive here!

422
00:26:06,063 --> 00:26:07,714
Oh!

423
00:26:07,714 --> 00:26:10,136
Luckily, Mr. Yoon is here!

424
00:26:10,136 --> 00:26:12,503
Oh, what brought you here?

425
00:26:12,503 --> 00:26:16,701
She wanted to see where her son worked.

426
00:26:16,701 --> 00:26:18,324
So we came.

427
00:26:18,849 --> 00:26:20,646
Excuse me.

428
00:26:22,179 --> 00:26:23,270
Huh?

429
00:26:26,395 --> 00:26:27,554
Huh?

430
00:26:31,001 --> 00:26:32,648
Are you the director?

431
00:26:32,761 --> 00:26:35,103
You work for Se Yoon?

432
00:26:37,797 --> 00:26:39,530
How do you know...

433
00:26:39,530 --> 00:26:41,165
What happened to my son?

434
00:26:41,165 --> 00:26:43,277
Why are you still here when my son isn't?

435
00:26:43,277 --> 00:26:45,765
It wasn't me...

436
00:26:57,292 --> 00:26:58,661
Oh...

437
00:26:59,938 --> 00:27:01,757
What... what is it?

438
00:27:09,077 --> 00:27:10,174
Hmm?

439
00:27:24,377 --> 00:27:25,824
Perhaps this is...

440
00:27:26,659 --> 00:27:28,588
That belongs to Mr. Son.

441
00:27:28,588 --> 00:27:33,009
Oh... Se Yoon is asking
me to find him quickly.

442
00:27:33,009 --> 00:27:35,931
He's shouting, "Mom, find me!"

443
00:27:35,931 --> 00:27:37,174
Se Yoon!

444
00:27:45,064 --> 00:27:47,673
Is this Choong Shin Construction
that invested in the movie?

445
00:27:47,673 --> 00:27:49,097
Yes, it is.

446
00:27:49,150 --> 00:27:51,223
Oh, he's coming here!

447
00:27:51,442 --> 00:27:52,961
Gi Bum!

448
00:27:53,057 --> 00:27:54,126
Oh!

449
00:27:55,307 --> 00:27:56,673
What brought you here?

450
00:27:56,673 --> 00:28:00,335
This is the man, who I told you
was really close to your son!

451
00:28:00,796 --> 00:28:02,182
Who is she?

452
00:28:03,710 --> 00:28:05,713
She's Mr. Son's mother.

453
00:28:06,713 --> 00:28:07,876
What?

454
00:28:07,876 --> 00:28:09,869
Something happened between
you and my son, right?

455
00:28:11,486 --> 00:28:14,584
What do you mean? It's just
that things went wrong...

456
00:28:15,060 --> 00:28:17,859
He did it first... I didn't
do that intentionally...

457
00:28:26,338 --> 00:28:28,451
Just tell her the truth.

458
00:28:28,451 --> 00:28:31,229
You spilled hot soup over his pants.

459
00:28:31,463 --> 00:28:33,398
His thigh was burned a little.

460
00:28:33,398 --> 00:28:37,532
Yes, it was my fault... hot soup...
his thigh...

461
00:28:37,532 --> 00:28:39,250
Is that all?

462
00:28:41,278 --> 00:28:43,411
Well... that's...

463
00:28:43,411 --> 00:28:47,005
Gi Bum, you always did that.
You still do that?

464
00:28:47,005 --> 00:28:48,761
You should be more careful.

465
00:28:48,761 --> 00:28:50,932
Oh, yes.

466
00:28:52,159 --> 00:28:55,848
I am going to pray in
Gyeryong Mountain tonight.

467
00:28:58,571 --> 00:29:02,538
I am sure... I will get an answer.

468
00:29:11,842 --> 00:29:14,537
Did you buy whipped cream
and condensed milk?

469
00:29:14,974 --> 00:29:16,880
Okay, I got it.

470
00:29:19,962 --> 00:29:21,388
Come on in!

471
00:29:35,669 --> 00:29:37,599
I'll close the store for a moment.

472
00:29:42,119 --> 00:29:43,582
Why did you come back?

473
00:29:44,230 --> 00:29:47,732
My contract didn't say I couldn't
come back to my hometown.

474
00:29:47,732 --> 00:29:50,099
You are still arrogant.

475
00:29:50,786 --> 00:29:52,324
You didn't change a bit.

476
00:29:52,992 --> 00:29:55,681
Don't even think about
ruining my son's life.

477
00:29:55,914 --> 00:29:57,478
Just go back while I'm still nice.

478
00:29:57,478 --> 00:30:01,608
Do you still think
I ruined Gi Bum's life?

479
00:30:01,608 --> 00:30:05,710
You should be thankful that I let
you keep the money and your child!

480
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:09,040
What the heck are you trying
to do, using your child?

481
00:30:09,768 --> 00:30:11,275
Is it money?

482
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,275
Think what you like.

483
00:30:14,275 --> 00:30:16,198
Aren't you embarrassed to your child?

484
00:30:16,228 --> 00:30:19,954
No, I have nothing to be
ashamed of or afraid of.

485
00:30:19,954 --> 00:30:22,126
You're doing this for your child, right?

486
00:30:22,396 --> 00:30:23,848
It's likewise.

487
00:30:24,201 --> 00:30:26,717
I won't let you kick me out like before!

488
00:30:27,373 --> 00:30:28,576
How dare!

489
00:30:28,576 --> 00:30:32,057
You kicked out all the
customers, and now it's us?

490
00:30:33,834 --> 00:30:34,856
Hyun Jee!

491
00:30:34,856 --> 00:30:36,943
What have we done so wrong?

492
00:30:36,943 --> 00:30:39,249
I asked her to move down here.

493
00:30:39,249 --> 00:30:41,138
Don't do this to my mom!

494
00:30:42,102 --> 00:30:44,648
Hyun Jee! Hyun Jee!

495
00:30:46,728 --> 00:30:47,932
Hyun Jee!

496
00:30:48,579 --> 00:30:49,727
Hyun Jee!

497
00:30:50,384 --> 00:30:52,606
Hyun Jee! Hyun Jee!

498
00:30:53,986 --> 00:30:55,314
Hyun Jee!

499
00:31:48,202 --> 00:31:51,131
Well, do you have an upbeat song?

500
00:31:51,377 --> 00:31:53,997
I'm totally gloomy today.

501
00:31:56,105 --> 00:31:57,157
Gosh.

502
00:31:57,777 --> 00:32:00,196
You're ignoring me again? Hey.

503
00:32:00,196 --> 00:32:02,386
Don't pretend to be so chic.

504
00:32:04,605 --> 00:32:07,919
I remember how dumb you
were when you were little.

505
00:32:13,250 --> 00:32:14,711
Hey!

506
00:32:14,711 --> 00:32:17,775
Stop bothering me!
I'm not interested in you!

507
00:32:25,088 --> 00:32:27,273
We are lovers from now on.

508
00:32:27,273 --> 00:32:30,330
It means I'm your owner
and you are my servant.

509
00:32:30,330 --> 00:32:32,171
If you understand, say yes.

510
00:32:32,171 --> 00:32:33,861
Yes, Hyun Jee.

511
00:32:36,373 --> 00:32:39,174
Do you remember it now?

512
00:32:43,946 --> 00:32:45,862
It's not enough pretending
to be a singer?

513
00:32:45,862 --> 00:32:47,777
Now you're making a movie?

514
00:32:47,876 --> 00:32:50,112
Is she your girlfriend?

515
00:32:50,112 --> 00:32:52,125
Wow, she's...

516
00:32:52,955 --> 00:32:54,213
Cute!

517
00:32:56,587 --> 00:32:57,656
Let's go.

518
00:32:57,656 --> 00:33:00,856
Bastard! You ignore us again?

519
00:33:00,856 --> 00:33:02,382
Hey!

520
00:33:02,454 --> 00:33:04,468
You better just go your way.

521
00:33:04,787 --> 00:33:06,153
I'm not in a good mood today.

522
00:33:06,153 --> 00:33:07,795
Bitch!

523
00:33:09,287 --> 00:33:10,501
You!

524
00:33:10,959 --> 00:33:12,344
Hey!

525
00:33:14,965 --> 00:33:16,396
I can't see!

526
00:33:17,294 --> 00:33:18,515
Cops!

527
00:33:19,848 --> 00:33:22,151
Oh, Sung Min! Sung Min!

528
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:23,308
What?

529
00:33:24,122 --> 00:33:26,294
What happened to your face?

530
00:33:26,672 --> 00:33:29,505
What on earth happened?

531
00:33:29,505 --> 00:33:30,623
I'm fine, Mom.

532
00:33:30,623 --> 00:33:32,441
You are not fine at all!

533
00:33:32,441 --> 00:33:35,275
You should've been at cram school!
Why are you here?

534
00:33:36,747 --> 00:33:37,921
Hyun Jee!

535
00:33:38,340 --> 00:33:39,442
Hyun Jee?

536
00:33:39,679 --> 00:33:41,462
What's wrong? Are you okay?

537
00:33:41,462 --> 00:33:42,926
Aren't you hurt?

538
00:33:45,801 --> 00:33:46,865
Man!

539
00:33:47,013 --> 00:33:49,479
It seems that those kids bothered them.

540
00:33:49,598 --> 00:33:51,178
We already got the story.

